threads.title: 820-2850 no green light at magSafe, does not alloy
threads.message:
I don't know what translation software use, but is very poor.

Post SYS_ONEWIRE level and check continuity from U6900 to central pin of Magsafe connector.
Did you try other DCIN board?

threads.title: 820-2850 no green light at magSafe, does not alloy
threads.message:
SYS_ONEWIRE 1.15V. I have continuity from the component to the connector.

"Did you try other DCIN board?" I tested one that I am sure works.


[URL unfurl="true"]https://www.deepl.com/translator[/URL]

threads.title: 820-2850 no green light at magSafe, does not alloy
threads.message:
"SYS_ONEWIRE 1.15V"
Bad value.

Post diode mode to ground.
Check R5075; if good, reball SMC.

threads.title: 820-2850 no green light at magSafe, does not alloy
threads.message: I performed the SMC reball.  tested in SYS_ONEWIRE 0.625V diode mode.  There is no R5075.  no results.

threads.title: 820-2850 no green light at magSafe, does not alloy
threads.message:
"There is no R5075"
Yeah, that is true; check R6929 instead.

Post U6900/1 voltages.
